@node ESS_Introduction
@prev main
@next ESS_Requirements

                                           @{b}Introduction@{ub}

   Essence is a collection of textures for Imagine by Steve Worley and Apex. Essence is
   composed by two volumes and all the textures were written to work with Imagine 2.0.
   When Imagine 2.9 came out, the texture's format was changed so all the Essence's
   textures didn't work with this version of Imagine.
   Someone noticed that the only two differences were:

   1. Imagine 2.9+ needs the .itx extension for all the textures
   2. A byte was changed in the texture's format from $10 to $20

   @{b}EssencED@{ub} is a little CLI based utility for all Imagine and Essence Vol I/II users.
   It changes byte $FF (255) (for Essence Vol I) or byte $5f (for Essence Vol II) from $10 to $20
   to allow compatibility with Imagine 2.9+.

   EssencED has been written in C and compiled with StormC 1.1.

@endnode

@node ESS_Requirements
@prev ESS_Introduction
@next ESS_Usage

                                      @{b}Requirements@{ub}

      EssencED needs an Amiga with at least kickstart 1.3 (!!!!!!!!!!).
      Oh, you need Imagine 2.9+ and Essence Vol I/II (not both required) too...

@endnode

@node ESS_Usage
@prev ESS_Requirements
@next ESS_History

                                      @{b}Usage@{ub}

   @{b}WARNING! Make sure to make a copy of the original Essence Volume I/II disks.@{ub}

   EssencED is very simple to use:

   EssencED [-1] [-2] [AUTO] input-file output-file

   Input-file must be a texture provided with Essence Volume I.
   Output-file must be a new file with .itx extension... (now you can use the AUTO option!!!)

   -1 forces EssencED to change byte $ff in the texture. This option is the default choice
      for EssencED, so you can ignore it.
      @{b}Do not use this option on a Essence Vol II texture!@{ub}

   -2 forces EssencED to change byte $5f in the texture.
      Use this option @{b}only@{ub} if you want to make working an Essence Vol II texture with Imagine 2.9+!

   @{b}AUTO@{ub} This option is very useful if you want to save changed file with the same name,
   except for the extension (.itx). Using this option is not necessary specifying the output
   file name.

   You have to insert all the needed arguments or EssencED will print a usage message.

   If output file already exists, don't worry, EssencED will print an error message and
   it will exits without overwriting the existing file. 

@endnode

@node ESS_History
@prev ESS_Usage
@next ESS_Todo

                             @{b}History@{ub}

   V1.2 (14.10.1997) - Added AUTO option to save automatically the input file file as
                      inputfile-name.itx

   V1.1 (26.9.1997)  - Second public release
                     - Both the Essence volumes are supported

   V1.0 (25.9.1997)  - First public release
                     - Essence Volume I support
                     - CLI based version

@endnode
         
